# Contributing Guidelines

Thank you for considering contributing to this project!

All contributions are welcome, including:

- Bug reports
- Bug fixes
- Documentation improvements
- Enhancements
- New ideas and suggestions

## How to Contribute

1. Fork the repository
2. Create a new branch for your feature or fix
3. Make your changes
4. Commit your work with clear messages
5. Push to your forked repository
6. Submit a Pull Request

## Reporting Issues

If you find a bug or have a suggestion, please open an issue and provide as much detail as possible.

## Coding Standards

Please write clean, readable, and well-documented code. Make sure your changes do not break existing functionality.

## Pull Requests

Before submitting a pull request:

- Ensure your code works correctly
- Test your changes
- Update documentation if necessary

## Community

By contributing to this project, you agree to follow the project's Code of Conduct and maintain a respectful and collaborative environment.

Thank you for helping improve this project!
